    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "##  🔍Teacher Tip\r\n**Welcome to AI Chat Lab**. Use AI Chat Lab to generate several outcomes to complete the sentence.\r\n\r\nYou can keep prompting AI Chat using the same prompt or follow up by prompting it to \"generate three more answers\". While you chat, think about *How does AI's output compare to the word you predicted?*\r\n\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 18px; font-weight: bold; background-color: #F5F7F8; padding: 10px; border-left: 5px solid #8148B2; display: inline-block;\">➡️ This level is from Lesson 1. You can find more details in the full <a href='https://studio.code.org/s/aif1-2025/lessons/1' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer' style='text-decoration: none; font-weight: bold;'>Lesson Plan</a>.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Finish the Sentence\r\n\r\nUse AI Chat to finish the sentence.\r\n\r\n### Do This:\r\n1. Think about how you would complete the following sentence with a single word: *\"The dog barked at the...\"*\r\n2. **Copy and paste** the following prompt: \r\n\r\n>Complete this sentence with a single word: The dog barked at the...\r\n3. Press **Send**.\r\n4. Then read **AI Chat's response** and compare it to your own.\r\n\r\n**Try it out!**\r\n",
